mechanical installation paying attention to how every detail of the project relates to each other.','Services Page Intro','','publish','closed','closed','','services-page-intro','','','2016-06-29 19:19:52','2016-06-29 19:19:52','',0,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/?page_id=185',0,'page','',0),(186,3,'2016-06-29 19:12:07','2016-06-29 19:12:07','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Crown Jade design focuses on personalized design for new and remodel projects in residential and commercial fields which includes code compliant design, architectural drafting, and full structural analysis.</span>\r\n\r\nCrown Jade has a strong interest in green sustainable housing design with emphasis on energy efficient integrated design. Integrated design means thinking through the entire project from the foundation to mechanical installation paying attention to how every detail of the project relates to each other.','Services Page Intro','','inherit','closed','closed','','185-revision-v1','','','2016-06-29 19:12:07','2016-06-29 19:12:07','',185,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/2016/06/29/185-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(187,3,'2016-06-29 19:34:35','2016-06-29 19:34:35','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Crown Jade is an architectural design, drafting, and structural engineering firm specializing in energy efficient design and alternative construction method design. We personally design in-house, the complete plan-sets required to obtain a new home or renovation permit. </span>\r\n\r\nCrown Jade design focuses on personalized design for new and remodel projects in residential and commercial fields which includes code compliant design, architectural drafting and full structural analysis.\r\n\r\nIntegrated design means thinking through the entire project from the foundation to mechanical installation paying attention to how every detail of the project relates to each other. We have an extensive background in construction with experience from residential to commercial building allowing them to create a unified vision for all projects.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The process begins by recognizing and understanding desires and helping you work through your design, whether it be a napkin sketch or drawn plans on graph paper. Next we offer design suggestions, identify problem areas, and ensure code compliance in your design. Each set of completed plans includes a plot plan, 3-D rendering, construction build set, full engineering, and full support throughout the build process.</span>\r\n\r\nWith over 30 years of construction knowledge we have established this firm to provide you with the best service possible through our hands-on home-building experience and our formal education. Our experience spans virtually every aspect of construction, architecture, and engineering, as well as specializing in the development of Passive House, SIPs, log, timber, and other homes that utilize alternative building methods. We tackle projects other engineers, without our experience, find too challenging. We provide engineering along with architectural drafting, all at a competitive price that will fit within your fee structure.\r\n\r\nThe Dream is within reach. Let us help you get there.','Company','','publish','closed','closed','','about','','','2016-06-29 19:56:07','2016-06-29 19:56:07','',0,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/?page_id=187',0,'page','',0),(188,3,'2016-06-29 19:34:35','2016-06-29 19:34:35','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Crown Jade is an architectural design, drafting, and structural engineering firm specializing in energy efficient design and alternative construction method design. We personally design in-house, the complete plan-sets required to obtain a new home or renovation permit. </span>\r\n\r\nCrown Jade design focuses on personalized design for new and remodel projects in residential and commercial fields which includes code compliant design, architectural drafting and full structural analysis.\r\n\r\nIntegrated design means thinking through the entire project from the foundation to mechanical installation paying attention to how every detail of the project relates to each other. We have an extensive background in construction with experience from residential to commercial building allowing them to create a unified vision for all projects.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The process begins by recognizing and understanding desires and helping you work through your design, whether it be a napkin sketch or drawn plans on graph paper. Next we offer design suggestions, identify problem areas, and ensure code compliance in your design. Each set of completed plans includes a plot plan, 3-D rendering, construction build set, full engineering, and full support throughout the build process.</span>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','187-revision-v1','','','2016-06-29 19:34:35','2016-06-29 19:34:35','',187,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/2016/06/29/187-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(189,3,'2016-06-29 19:40:09','2016-06-29 19:40:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','company','','','2016-06-29 20:00:00','2016-06-29 20:00:00','',0,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/?p=189',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(191,3,'2016-06-29 19:43:12','2016-06-29 19:43:12','Daniel was born and raised in Fort Collins, Colorado. Growing up he always enjoyed taking advantage of\r\n\r\nthe many outdoor activities that the Colorado Mountains have to offer including hiking, camping,\r\n\r\nsnowboarding, and mountain biking. This love of the outdoors led to his passion to protect the precious\r\n\r\nnatural areas and resources that we have. After a brief stint playing junior hockey in Minneapolis,\r\n\r\nMinnesota, Daniel moved back to Fort Collins to attend Colorado State University (CSU), where he\r\n\r\nstudied Civil Engineering. In 2012 Daniel and his senior design team won third place in the Engineering\r\n\r\nDays Senior Design Showcase for the school of Civil and Environmental Engineering. Their project was\r\n\r\nthe development of a web based platform that could estimate solar panel production and payoff using a\r\n\r\nGoogle Maps interface. Daniel obtained his BS in Civil Engineering with a minor in business from CSU in\r\n\r\nthe spring of 2013. After graduation Daniel worked as a Civil Engineer designing cell phone towers.\r\n\r\nDaniel joined the Crown Jade team in the spring of 2015. His draw to the company was being able to\r\n\r\npractice Civil Engineering while working for a company that integrates sustainable solutions by using\r\n\r\nalternative materials and design methods. Daniel looks forward to continuing to grow with Crown Jade\r\n\r\nand promoting sustainable building solutions that lessen the impact on our earth.','Daniel Jobson','','inherit','closed','closed','','190-revision-v1','','','2016-06-29 19:43:12','2016-06-29 19:43:12','',190,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/2016/06/29/190-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(192,3,'2016-06-29 19:46:47','2016-06-29 19:46:47','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jerome Kommrusch grew up in Schaumberg, Illinois. As a young man he developed a love for Art and Architecture inspired by fond visits to log lodges and various visitor centers in Colorado and South Dakota. Motivated by these experiences and his love for wanting design he enrolled at William Rainey Harper College in Palatine, Illinois where he received an Associates Degree in Applied Sciences of Architectural Technology. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After completing his formal schooling, he settled in Fort Collins, CO where he began designing projects for Log Knowledge in Laporte, CO. His designs ranged from small hunting cabins and weekend getaways to multi-million dollar private homes all over the front range. His most notable achievement is designing the main clubhouse for the Pelican Lakes Country Club in Windsor, CO. His other achievements include Timber Frame Assembly drawings for Aspen Highlands Village in Aspen, CO, Lookout Mountain Nature Center in Golden, CO, and the Sylvan Dale Heritage Center in Loveland, CO.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jerome has comprehensive experience in multiple genres of design styles providing broad knowledge in his specialized design field allowing him to work effectively with builders, Engineers and Architects to achieve a quality design product. He takes his influences from the Arts and Crafts Movement as well as historical and modern joinery techniques in Scandinavian and Japanese styles which provide him a well-rounded repertoire of design elements to draw from.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jerome Kommrusch remains currently in Northern Colorado with his two beautiful children and close family. He enjoys the outdoors, cycling and gathering with friends over self-cooked gourmet meals.</span>','Jerome Kommrusch','','publish','closed','closed','','jerome-kommrusch','','','2016-06-29 19:46:47','2016-06-29 19:46:47','',0,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/?page_id=192',0,'page','',0),(193,3,'2016-06-29 19:46:47','2016-06-29 19:46:47','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jerome Kommrusch grew up in Schaumberg, Illinois. As a young man he developed a love for Art and Architecture inspired by fond visits to log lodges and various visitor centers in Colorado and South Dakota. Motivated by these experiences and his love for wanting design he enrolled at William Rainey Harper College in Palatine, Illinois where he received an Associates Degree in Applied Sciences of Architectural Technology. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After completing his formal schooling, he settled in Fort Collins, CO where he began designing projects for Log Knowledge in Laporte, CO. His designs ranged from small hunting cabins and weekend getaways to multi-million dollar private homes all over the front range. His most notable achievement is designing the main clubhouse for the Pelican Lakes Country Club in Windsor, CO. His other achievements include Timber Frame Assembly drawings for Aspen Highlands Village in Aspen, CO, Lookout Mountain Nature Center in Golden, CO, and the Sylvan Dale Heritage Center in Loveland, CO.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jerome has comprehensive experience in multiple genres of design styles providing broad knowledge in his specialized design field allowing him to work effectively with builders, Engineers and Architects to achieve a quality design product. He takes his influences from the Arts and Crafts Movement as well as historical and modern joinery techniques in Scandinavian and Japanese styles which provide him a well-rounded repertoire of design elements to draw from.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jerome Kommrusch remains currently in Northern Colorado with his two beautiful children and close family. He enjoys the outdoors, cycling and gathering with friends over self-cooked gourmet meals.</span>','Jerome Kommrusch','','inherit','closed','closed','','192-revision-v1','','','2016-06-29 19:46:47','2016-06-29 19:46:47','',192,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/2016/06/29/192-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(194,3,'2016-06-29 19:47:29','2016-06-29 19:47:29','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Daniel was born and raised in Fort Collins, Colorado. Growing up he always enjoyed taking advantage of the many outdoor activities that the Colorado Mountains have to offer including hiking, camping, snowboarding, and mountain biking. This love of the outdoors led to his passion to protect the precious natural areas and resources that we have. After a brief stint playing junior hockey in Minneapolis, Minnesota, Daniel moved back to Fort Collins to attend Colorado State University (CSU), where he studied Civil Engineering. In 2012 Daniel and his senior design team won third place in the Engineering Days Senior Design Showcase for the school of Civil and Environmental Engineering. Their project was the development of a web based platform that could estimate solar panel pr