sed his priorities and decided to pick up where left off with his schooling years previous. He moved to Flagstaff, AZ with his now large family, enrolling himself in Northern Arizona University where he earned a Bachelor’s of Science in Civil Engineering degree. Longing for the Colorado mountains they moved back to Fort Collins where he and his sons built the family home. He became a Registered Professional Engineer in 2004, founding Crown Jade Design and Engineering with his third son, Chief Drafter and Designer David Benjamin. Together they are continuing with his original ideals of making a difference in the world with the goal of doing this through the sustainable designs they produce. Mark received his Master of Engineering degree from CSU in 2010. He is also a Certified Passive House consultant. His interests include taking his children to car shows, love of music (volunteering his time for local events) and anything outdoors including skiing.','Mark Benjamin','','inherit','closed','closed','','206-revision-v1','','','2016-06-29 20:06:26','2016-06-29 20:06:26','',206,'http://tlchatt.com/crownjade/2016/06/29/206-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(206,3,'2016-06-29 20:06:26','2016-06-29 20:06:26','Mark Benjamin grew up in Michigan as a peace loving hippie of the ‘70’s. Facing the challenges of the real world with a growing family he didn’t abandon his ideals of making a better earth and better environment for his children. With the birth of his first son he settled in Fort Collins, CO and started on the path to make this desire a reality by enrolling at Colorado State University (CSU) majoring in Engineering Science for Solar Engineering. With the pressures of a growing family he had to put his schooling on pause, moved back home to Michigan and began a career in construction. He has worked a total of 35 years in construction with experience ranging from carpentry, foreman, superintendent and Project Manager in both residential and commercial fields. Following a 